The area

Address
Neighborhood: Bairro Alto, Bica & Cais do Sodré
Enjoy a cocktail, discover a jazz club, hit the dance floor or simply grab a beer and catch up with your friends in the street: Bairro Alto, Bica and Cais do Sodré are the core of it all. Amazing rooftops, restaurants, cafes, bars, art galleries, museums and theaters abound. Start off by admiring the river from the Santa Catarina belvedere, have a cocktail at PARK's rooftop bar, try a typical Portuguese steak, or the fresh grilled fish, at Príncipe do Calhariz, and later explore the dozens of streets full of bars and clubs! Whether you're visiting for a day or a whole week, make sure you visit Bairro Alto and its surroundings.
How to get there
  • Cais do Sodré • 6 min walk
  • Baixa/Chiado • 10 min walk

This is a dud if you have been to any of the other miradouros in Lisbon unless you like to see tiled roof tops. But it seems to be a good place to hang out as the grassy slope behind the viewing platform was filled to the brim with people just lying there seemingly enjoying people watching. If you have other more interesting places to explore, this is one place you can safely skip.

Don't bother, no view
Oct 2019 • Couples
We had read so much about this place and were really excited to see the view from this vantage point. To get there, you have to walk precariously down a very steep hill and then drag yourselves up a dozen exhausting steps (as is the case in much of Lisbon). Once you get there, you will be disappointed to see that there is virtually no vista at all, if you call peeping through a fence blocked by buildings a vista. Don't waste your time.
